'''Niels Marnegrave''' (born December 9, 1987) is a Belgian [[basketball]] player for [[Spirou Charleroi]].

==Career==
Marnegrave debuted on the professional level in the 2004–05 season for [[Liège Basket]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurocupbasketball.com/eurocup/competition/players/showplayer?pcode=JTB&clubcode=OOS&gamecode=169&seasoncode=U2013 |title=MARNEGRAVE, NIELS - Welcome to Eurocup |publisher=Eurocupbasketball.com |date=1987-12-09 |accessdate=2014-04-24}}</ref>

After his debut season he signed with [[Dexia Mons-Hainaut]]. In 2006 he won the [[Belgian Basketball Cup|Belgian Cup]] with the team.

In the 2009–10 season Marnegrave played for [[RBC Verviers-Pepinster]].

He signed a 3-year contract with the [[Leuven Bears]] in 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.leuvenbears.be/content/niels-marnegrave-sluit-een-contract-van-drie-jaar-af-bij-leuven-bears |title=Niels Marnegrave sluit een contract van drie jaar af bij Leuven Bears &#124; Leuven Bears |publisher=Leuvenbears.be |date=2012-02-13 |accessdate=2014-04-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140424155940/http://www.leuvenbears.be/content/niels-marnegrave-sluit-een-contract-van-drie-jaar-af-bij-leuven-bears |archivedate=2014-04-24 |df= }}</ref> In the 2012–13 season, Marnegrave averaged 11.7 points per game and led the [[List of Ethias League season steals leaders|league in steals]] with 2.4 per game.

Marnegrave signed with defending Belgian champion [[BC Oostende|Telenet BC Oostende]] for the 2013–14 season. He still played there in 2014-2015 and 2015-2016 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportando.com/en/cat/nba/101155/niels-marnegrave-pierre-antoine-gillet-will-play-with-oostende.html |title=Niels Marnegrave, Pierre-Antoine Gillet will play with Oostende |publisher=Sportando.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-24}}</ref>

On June 9, 2016, Marnegrave signed with [[Spirou Charleroi]].<ref>[http://www.sportando.com/en/europe/belgium/201679/spirou-charleroi-inks-niels-marnegrave.html Spirou Charleroi inks Niels Marnegrave]</ref>

==Honors==
*[[Belgian Basketball League|Belgian League]] (3): 2014, 2015, 2016
*[[Belgian Basketball Cup|Belgian Cup]] (4): 2006, 2014, 2015, 2016
;Individual awards
*[[List of Basketball League Belgium Division I season assists leaders|Belgian League assists leader]] (1): [[2015–16 Belgian Basketball League|2016]]

